</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uradiation911.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Radiation911</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/11/02 3:05:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=582.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blizzard.com/images/war3/units/dreadlord.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grieg...</span><hr size=1> Remember to hide the clerics in the room with the portal to Grieg's so they can be safe from the knockback which interrupts your casting. <br>
<br>
MTing works fine, just have the MT in the same group as the clerics so they can see his health. You don't even need a CH rotation, just heal the MT as needed. The only damage he does is the 1200 blind proc, the 600 AE knockback, and the 300 AE snare. Your MA will be getting hit with these the entire fight as even if your MR is incredibly high you're not going to resist that many.<br>
Your other melees and casters should learn to avoid these. This fight is all about positioning. <br>
<br>
His melee is incredibly weak and he can also be slowed which is very important as he has lots of HPs so it's a long fight. Defensive is not needed.  <br>
<br>
The first time we tried Grieg we threw 30 people at him and got smoked. We all got knockbacked into the same corner and no one could get out and he just slowly melee'd us all to death. Spent a good five minutes laughing my ass off after this fight.<br>
<br>
Next day we came back, worked on our strategy, and the only person that died was the chanter who tashed too early.<br>
This is definitely my favorite fight on Luclin, it's much more fun that auto attack on and watching TV like on THO or in Ssra.<br>
